  "title": "Adding multiple values to facets",
  "body": "Hi! I have a documentation issue on InstantSearch.js, I could not find what I was looking for which is how to implement a function to template > item in a refinementList as seen here: https://www.algolia.com/product\r\n\r\nThe actors have images attached to the names, I'm trying to archive this, but apparently the only options here are label, highlighted, value, count, isRefined, url (as documented).\r\n\r\nThis is my current refinementList. Within templates > item, all 3 (label, highlighted, value) output the same thing.\r\n\r\n```\r\nsearch.addWidget(\r\n\t\tinstantsearch.widgets.refinementList({\r\n\t\t\tcontainer: '#darsteller',\r\n\t\t\tattributeName: 'darsteller.name',\r\n\t\t\tsortBy: [\"isRefined\",\"name:asc\"],\r\n\t\t\toperator: 'and',\r\n\t\t\tlimit: 12,\r\n\t\t\tshowMore: {\r\n\t\t\t\ttemplates: {\r\n\t\t\t\t\tactive: '<div class=\"showless\">weniger anzeigen</div>',\r\n\t\t\t\t\tinactive: '<div class=\"showmore\">mehr anzeigen</div>'\r\n\t\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\t},\r\n\t\t\ttemplates: {\r\n\t\t\t\theader: 'Darsteller',\r\n\t\t\t\titem: '{{label}}, {{highlighted}}, {{value}}'\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t})\r\n\t);\r\n```\r\n\r\nHow do I accomplish something like shown in the demo (link provided on top)?",
